1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,708
Here is how, simply.

2
00:00:01,658 --> 00:00:06,458
The manager turns your goal into a typed plan — a DAG, a flowchart of tasks with the right order built in.

3
00:00:06,458 --> 00:00:13,750
A deterministic orchestrator runs that plan: it routes each step to the right specialist, and checks every hand-off against a contract — so each output is valid input for the next.

4
00:00:13,750 --> 00:00:17,050
Guardrails cap time and cost, and risky steps wait for your approval.

5
00:00:17,050 --> 00:00:21,166
Every move lands in an append-only event log — so the whole run is auditable and replayable.

6
00:00:21,166 --> 00:00:25,158
The creative parts stay creative; the coordination stays deterministic, auditable code.

